    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed the required level for a Medium model risk, Medium decision consequence COU. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved level 2 vs. required level 3) is accepted because the tested condition is the most clinically representative load case, all three QoIs satisfy the pre-defined quantitative acceptance criteria (E/uval < 1.96, mean difference < 10%), and the overall evidence package provides sufficient confidence to support the regulatory submission decision. The credibility assessment team unanimously accepted the package.",
